		(uuid "049aa27d-1c10-4cf3-9597-42c09c31df89")
	)
	(text "1) INSTALL JUMPER (PN: JM-2BK-61 OR SIMILAR) ACROSS JP1 TO ENABLE RS485.\n     REMOVE JUMPER TO PROGRAM PRO MICRO VIA USB.\n\n    CAUTION: POWER SUPPLY PINS ON BUS OUT CONNECTOR WILL BE ACTIVE \n    REGARDLESS IF DATA IS ENABLED ON THAT CONNECTOR.\n\n2) RS485 BUS TERMINATION: DO NOT INSTALL J2 (BUS OUT) CONNECTOR \n    AND ADD A 120OHM THRU-HOLE RESISTOR ACROSS PINS 4&5 OF J2 \n    (BUS OUT) ON LAST SLAVE DEVICE OF RS485 BUS.\n\n3) ABSIS RS485 BUS SPECIFICATION\n   3.1) BUS IS HALF DUPLEX: EITHER TRANSMITTING OR RECIEVING AT ANY GIVEN TIME.\n   3.2) PIN FUNCTION: R: DATA OUTPUT / D: DATA INPUT / DE HAS INTERNAL PULL-DOWN \n        (DRIVER DISABLED BY DEFAULT) / RE HAS INTERNAL PULL-UP (RECIEVER DISABLED BY DEFAULT)\n   3.3) CIRCUIT CONTAINS OPEN, SHORT, AND IDLE BUS FAILSAFE WHICH PREVENTS THE SYSTEM FROM \n        INTERPRETING ELECTRICAL NOISE AS VALID DATA.\n   3.4) THVD1410DR TRANSCIEVER OPERATES WITH TTL LEVEL INPUTS. (LOGIC HIGH: 2V - VCC / \n        LOGIC LOW: 0V - .8VCC)\n   3.5) CAUTION: AS CABLE LENGTH INCREASES, DATA RATE DECREASES PROPORTIONALLY."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 14.732 66.802 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.524 1.524)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "1b27456e-d8ae-445c-80f7-a181d8ab89a6")
	)
	(text "NOTES: (UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED)"
